[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring Java Serialization Handling**\n\nI'm thinking about handling the readObject call and how it may raise a ClassCastException with a String stream. It's interesting that Java can deserialize Strings natively. However, it seems like native errors are related to how the String.serialVersionUID is read reflectively in certain tests. Strings have a unique serialization token, TC_STRING, which means that when I call output.writeObject(\"x\"), it writes TC_STRING, and input.readObject just returns the String without needing a constructor.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0b8fffa4bb7d9de90169fc13eff8c08194947dd8fefc5cbfb0\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_BQD_SdOhTiBAvUF6czvqXKYgqEJvXwqwxiij2k2fp-h95jsJw2L-ao5PjiEUJlQ9lviW2dSdetfIBUOXxggatCri_b-rhA3O6ohkEiWQR7mMTQTig0xcOKJEI1_2TNhDCXZEKzwKRw1vhGvC0fGMxuzM16Gk4O5C70fYp3xdWZ_YwBvom07KLV5msFxvLgrQ7UKVdTdYk1Q0gDQz3pLOgwqq5vHpR3ZHaAyXp4X-q63mjrCGiGi3ecrIkbYLUMcAkZaHMPTYN1p7lEv0NXQbVtA0OV1dMu7ZIJPzO218jQbWQAjOFel9IXe5ueCtRM20C1zdfwvs0m-lC35Ttzt0ImFMdYqf1BZVfaqJHV3HiF-AKf1zc0PWz1IihffRUejt4l8PrgIY7jxDgMJK4Xp1HyIDIO-ddzGQ6BuyX7Gg8tD4gqFVmacAW-W03OIaKQM4HTMziv3UwU7_2O2olTQql9N89tBLCN5-AqB0SLSYJzBB9nFEaQ9JN2k6XAlgPavp2xyaVmtCEZDbZojv3wra4eXpcItSKnvFpjBuIzCqVbH3_hcUYtnLGu2KV5bW39B_jhkPn-i8hsOzKRxTEzOvjKrPwjySRY46K-VqPzdeeJxq2eZBqj_m0Hi4azWU54reSPcO3NxBI2UrI_xKh6YfCu_KWmG3-ZMA0XvVJwwD5Ob3COtKMrCatVRFXHGjh3OFzQHraSSGGaUpIBliH8B8Asi0qdsqtMCZ_8xwPWo1-PltDB-fzATfV3es18H6cAtDno_SJqvkKqzO11K1XqUq-3EGAtqJyjM2GREPP6RRJKQ5p98pt3s4he4v9E3pgndys6x7KuHfkudfj1KqKcuu3VM28IxNhWsa-vwWGVa8vJoY0hqnprUbGji2eEF5V3D0yrZ7Y9_tAbgH_9LLzZ7kzA7GTxJ_KlXK8teq1alGBgai2xEMLWNXPLxFRPAD4vRtwXhLRImuCNT1K5bJceWIhKh2FTTIRGu5s_hgw2VuYdo61uZzpbyhNmqO2o42AtnqSBMcWvjvhA0zRBFJsg8Ok6-oAyKRbykATtbj7-JCAKmzvGV7rC68LKsZLN8wTTRAa2MBn-aO-szrM5JBTn7ZUpgidV-II-SKTlRSHtXWtBji_R_NYq5hpwh-uMbobVjVgLUij-I6xjsofWNhzOQqNTD7zX1tY9uKW8yxn5ivJ4PZi3w